# Pimeleon Builder Vulnerability Suppressions
# These CVEs affect upstream Debian packages but either have no available fix
# in Bookworm or do not impact the integrity of cross-compiled binaries.

# Git: Code execution / file writes (Local builder context limits risk)
CVE-2025-48384
CVE-2025-48385

# libarchive: Infinite Loop / DoS
CVE-2026-4111

# glibc: Heap corruption via memalign
CVE-2026-0861

# libexpat: Integer overflow / DoS
CVE-2026-25210

# openldap: Null pointer dereference
CVE-2023-2953

# Mbed TLS: Use-after-free / Integer Overflow / Null pointer / Race condition
CVE-2025-47917
CVE-2024-23775
CVE-2025-48965
CVE-2025-52496

# Python 3.11: Command injection / DoS (Used for build scripting only)
CVE-2025-13836
CVE-2025-15366
CVE-2025-15367
CVE-2025-69534
CVE-2025-8194
CVE-2026-1299

# SQLite3: Integer overflow
CVE-2025-7458

# Vim/xxd: Arbitrary code execution (Build tool only)
CVE-2026-25749
CVE-2026-26269
CVE-2026-28417
CVE-2026-28421

# zlib: Heap-based buffer overflow (Marked wont-fix by upstream)
CVE-2023-45853

# Kernel Headers (linux-libc-dev): Inert during build, applies to host kernel.
# Suppressing the package to manage the high volume of unresolved upstream CVEs.
linux-libc-dev
